article.headline: N. Arizona 64, W. Kentucky 61
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Josh Wilson hit a last-second 3-pointer to give Northern Arizona a 64-61 win over Western Kentucky on Saturday night. Wilson's one-handed, off-balance shot came with two-tenths of a second remaining after Orlando Mendez-Valdez had tied the score at 61 on a 3-pointer with seven seconds left. Nate Geiser scored 15 points to pace the Lumberjacks (4-3) while Kyle Landry added 14 points and 10 rebounds. Tyrone Brazelton and Mendez-Valdez each scored 14 points for Western Kentucky (5-2). Courtney Lee added 11 points for the Hilltoppers, who trailed 36-30 at halftime.
